{"questionId":"9728","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Ollie has installed security lights on the side of his house that are activated by a sensor.&nbsp;The sensor is located at point C directly above point D. The area covered by the sensor&nbsp;is shown by the shaded region enclosed by triangle ABC. The distance from A to B is&nbsp;4.5 m and the distance from B to C is 6 m. Angle AĈB is 15°.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/3b79976e7f92e61a9447f254373914497ae594d2.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Point B on the ground is 5 m from point E at the entrance to Ollie’s house. He is 1.8 m tall and&nbsp;is standing at point D, below the sensor. He walks towards point B.</p>\n<p>Find the distance Ollie is <strong>from the entrance to his house</strong> when he first activates&nbsp;the sensor.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{C}}\\mathop {\\text{B}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{D}} = 20.2 + 15 = 35.2^\\circ \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>B</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>D</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>20.2</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>15</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <msup>\n    <mn>35.2</mn>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>(let X be the point on BD where Ollie activates the sensor)</em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{tan}}\\,35.18741 \\ldots ^\\circ&nbsp; = \\frac{{1.8}}{{{\\text{BX}}}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>tan</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mn>35.18741</mn>\n  <msup>\n    <mo>…</mo>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.8</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>BX</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <strong><em>A1</em> </strong>for their correct angle <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{C}}\\mathop {\\text{B}}\\limits^ \\wedge&nbsp; {\\text{D}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mover>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>B</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>∧</mo>\n  </mover>\n  <mo>⁡</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>D</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>. Award <em><strong>M1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;correctly substituted trigonometric formula.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{BX}} = 2.55285 \\ldots \">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>BX</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2.55285</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5 - 2.55285 \\ldots \">\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2.55285</mn>\n  <mo>…</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>= 2.45 (m) (2.44714…)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9728","referenceCode":"SPM.1.SL.TZ0.14b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Point B on the ground is 5 m from point E at the entrance to Ollie’s house. He is 1.8 m tall and is standing at point D, below the sensor. He walks towards point B. Find the distan","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}